<paragraph blockId="5.[192,1440,1550,1929]" lastBlockId="6.[192,1440,1808,1928]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,323,1551,1575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martins, U. R. &amp; M. H. M. Galileo" box="[331,663,1551,1575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="53 - 95" refId="ref4348" refString="Martins, U. R., and M. H. M. Galileo. 1990. Onciderini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae): Sinonimias, novos taxons, chaves e notas. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia 37 (4): 53 - 95." type="journal article" year="1990">Martins and Galileo (1990)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins and Galileo" authorityYear="1990" box="[795,1060,1550,1574]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncioderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rondoniae">
<emphasis box="[795,1060,1550,1574]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Oncioderes rondoniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a single female specimen collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[333,449,1583,1607]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[464,543,1583,1607]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Brazil</collectingCountry>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Martins, U. R. &amp; M. H. M. Galileo" box="[561,887,1583,1607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="318 - 328" refId="ref4397" refString="Martins, U. R., and M. H. M. Galileo. 2013. Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) do Museu de Zoologia da Universidade Estadual de Feira de Santana, Bahia. Iheringia (Serie Zoologia) 103 (3): 318 - 328." type="journal article" year="2013">Martins and Galileo (2013)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins and Galileo" authorityYear="2013" box="[1014,1279,1582,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncioderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piauiensis">
<emphasis box="[1014,1279,1582,1606]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Oncioderes piauiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a single female specimen collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[553,618,1615,1639]" country="Brazil" name="Piaui" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Piauí</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[636,715,1615,1639]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Brazil</collectingCountry>
). In describing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins and Galileo" authorityYear="2013" box="[907,1069,1615,1638]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncioderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piauiensis">
<emphasis box="[907,1069,1615,1638]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">O. piauiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the authors provided the following to distinguish it from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins and Galileo" authorityYear="1990" box="[546,704,1647,1671]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncioderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rondoniae">
<emphasis box="[546,704,1647,1671]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">O. rondoniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[translated] “differs by the vertex with two small triangular pubescence chestnut spots and behind the eyes with orange pubescence; by whitish pronotal pubescence in the middle and more orange sides.” The key to four described species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1990" box="[1106,1240,1711,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncioderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1106,1240,1711,1735]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Oncioderes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; U. R. Martins &amp; A. Santos-Silva" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="99 - 110" refId="ref4300" refString="Galileo, M. H. M., U. R. Martins, and A. Santos-Silva. 2015. New species and new records in Ceram- bycidae (Coleoptera) of the state of Bahia, Brazil. ZooKeys 517: 99 - 110." type="journal article" year="2015">Galileo et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
reinforces that the difference between these two species is based solely only on color: the couplet separating the two species states that the elytral pubescence in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins and Galileo" authorityYear="2013" box="[1048,1211,1776,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncioderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piauiensis">
<emphasis box="[1048,1211,1776,1799]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">O. piauiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is “predominantly orangish-yellow” while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins and Galileo" authorityYear="1990" box="[497,649,1808,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncioderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rondoniae">
<emphasis box="[497,649,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">O. rondoniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is “predominantly yellowish-white.” Examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1440,1808,1832]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins and Galileo" authorityYear="1990" box="[347,614,1840,1864]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncioderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rondoniae">
<emphasis box="[347,614,1840,1864]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Oncioderes rondoniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MZSP) and a photograph of the 
<typeStatus box="[1037,1141,1840,1864]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins and Galileo" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncioderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piauiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Oncioderes piauiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(UEFS) revealed no morphological characters to separate the two species (
<figureCitation box="[1235,1304,1872,1896]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[192,275,1587,1609]" captionTargetBox="[369,1329,213,1553]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[369,1329,213,1553]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Four species of Onciderini. a) Microcanus minor (Bates, 1885), lectotype female, close-up of pronotum and elytral humeri. b) Oncideres paurosoma Noguera, 1993, paratype female, close-up of pronotum and elytral humeri. c) Microcanus minor (Bates, 1885), lectotype female, close-up of head. d) Oncideres paurosoma Noguera, 1993, paratype female, close-up of head. e) Oncioderes rondoniae Martins and Galileo, 1990, holotype female. f) Oncioderes piauiensis Martins and Galileo, 2013, holotype female. g) Oncioderes piauiensis Martins and Galileo, 2013, holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3673218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3673218/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
e–f). Based on close morphological similarities, 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins and Galileo, 2013" authorityName="Martins and Galileo" authorityYear="2013" box="[630,1224,1904,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncioderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piauiensis">
<emphasis box="[630,896,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Oncioderes piauiensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martins, U. R. &amp; M. H. M. Galileo" box="[903,1224,1904,1929]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="318 - 328" refId="ref4397" refString="Martins, U. R., and M. H. M. Galileo. 2013. Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) do Museu de Zoologia da Universidade Estadual de Feira de Santana, Bahia. Iheringia (Serie Zoologia) 103 (3): 318 - 328." type="journal article" year="2013">Martins and Galileo, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1259,1440,1904,1928]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">synonymized</emphasis>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins and Galileo, 1990" authorityName="Martins and Galileo" authorityYear="1990" box="[254,844,1808,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncioderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rondoniae">
<emphasis box="[254,517,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Oncioderes rondoniae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martins, U. R. &amp; M. H. M. Galileo" box="[523,844,1808,1832]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="53 - 95" refId="ref4348" refString="Martins, U. R., and M. H. M. Galileo. 1990. Onciderini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae): Sinonimias, novos taxons, chaves e notas. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia 37 (4): 53 - 95." type="journal article" year="1990">Martins and Galileo, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Note regarding the type locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins and Galileo" authorityYear="2013" box="[1274,1433,1808,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncioderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piauiensis">
<emphasis box="[1274,1433,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">O. piauiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: the latitude and longitude was incorrectly reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Martins, U. R. &amp; M. H. M. Galileo" box="[889,1230,1840,1864]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="318 - 328" refId="ref4397" refString="Martins, U. R., and M. H. M. Galileo. 2013. Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) do Museu de Zoologia da Universidade Estadual de Feira de Santana, Bahia. Iheringia (Serie Zoologia) 103 (3): 318 - 328." type="journal article" year="2013">Martins and Galileo (2013)</bibRefCitation>
as “ 
<geoCoordinate box="[1290,1436,1839,1864]" degrees="43" direction="south" minutes="29,391" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" precision="1" value="-43.48985">43°29,391′S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[192,346,1871,1896]" degrees="09" direction="west" minutes="13,228" orientation="longitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" precision="1" value="-9.220467">09°13,228′W</geoCoordinate>
″, which is located in the South Atlantic Ocean. Reversing the coordinates to “ 
<geoCoordinate box="[1290,1436,1871,1896]" degrees="09" direction="south" minutes="13,228" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" precision="1" value="-9.220467">09°13,228′S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[192,346,1903,1928]" degrees="43" direction="west" minutes="29,391" orientation="longitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" precision="1" value="-43.48985">43°29,391′W</geoCoordinate>
″, as indicated in the specimen label (
<figureCitation box="[800,887,1904,1928]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[192,275,1587,1609]" captionTargetBox="[369,1329,213,1553]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[369,1329,213,1553]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Four species of Onciderini. a) Microcanus minor (Bates, 1885), lectotype female, close-up of pronotum and elytral humeri. b) Oncideres paurosoma Noguera, 1993, paratype female, close-up of pronotum and elytral humeri. c) Microcanus minor (Bates, 1885), lectotype female, close-up of head. d) Oncideres paurosoma Noguera, 1993, paratype female, close-up of head. e) Oncioderes rondoniae Martins and Galileo, 1990, holotype female. f) Oncioderes piauiensis Martins and Galileo, 2013, holotype female. g) Oncioderes piauiensis Martins and Galileo, 2013, holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3673218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3673218/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[855,887,1904,1928]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" unit="g" value="2.0">2g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
), corrects the error.
</paragraph>
